EXAMPLE #2

Testing Gmail (test scenario steps for compose mail functionality)

1.	Verify that on clicking 'Compose' button, a frame to compose a mail gets displayed.
2.	Verify that user can enter emailIds in 'To', 'cc' and 'bcc' sections 
3.	Verify that user have suggestions while typing the emailds based on the existing emailIds in user's email list.
4.	Verify that user can enter multiple emails.
5.	Verify that user can type in the 'Subject' textbox.
6.	Verify that user can type the email in email section.
7.	Verify that user can format mail using editor-options provided like choosing font theme, font size, bold, italic, underline.
8.	Verify that user can attach file to the email.
9.	Verify that user can add images in the email.
10.	Verify that after entering  all mandatory fields, mail gets delivered to intended receivers.
11.	Verify that sent mails can be found in 'Sent Mail' sections.
12.	Verify that mail can be sent to non-gmail  emails.
13.	Verify that the emails composed but not sent remain in the draft section.
14.	Verify the maximum number of email recepients that can be entered in 'To', 'cc' and 'bcc' sections.
15.	Verify the maximum length of text that can be entered in the 'Subject' textbox.
16.	Verify the content limit of text/images that can be entered and successfully delivered as mail body.
17.	Verify the maximum size and number of attachement that can be attached with an email.

